THEVEIL!




Art by Elogee FishTruck and myself, respectively!



Isn't it just so convenient when some big idea you had on the backboard fits perfectly with the newest hit contest? #MassaTruthetts has been on my idea shelf for a long while. It just so happened to be perfect for this contest. It is historical for Massachusetts, and the United States, and the Foundation as a whole. It also covers the contest theme that I sorta wish had happened: victory. Here, the Foundation, while maybe not facing a huge threat, is undoubtedly victorious. I like that. Other things I liked about this draft:

Absolutely nothing is redacted or censored, except kind of that offset page.
There is no dialogue, there are no logs, it is a  SCP file.
I got to play heavily with the suspension of disbelief.


I don't have much else to say about this. Except maybe some spoilers. They probably are less spoiler-like than I think they are, to be honest. But I am going to put them under a collapsible anyways, for people who like .

Spoilers

Spoilers


This is the most meta article I have ever written.
The way  is referred to sounds like an agnostic's view on God.
I really hope that this upholds your suspension of disbelief.





EDIT: Huh. Critique did not reveal the second offset to be “racked on”. Interesting to see that coming out now. Anyways, probably not changing it. The article was written with the offset in mind, so it’s gonna stay that way. Upon consideration, moved the offset to just be in a collapsible, so it feels less disconnected.

EDIT the 2ND: I feel it is worth mentioning that this originated from a joke between myself and my IRL friend Tickilung, and he came up with it first I believe.





